This one can be dependently-typed, right? Something like
```
 (l.map fun x => ‚ü®x.1, f x.1 x.2‚ü© : List _).dlookup a = (l.dlookup a).map (f a) := by
 ```
Say the first list has type `List (Sigma Œ¥)`. What would the type of `f` be? I don't think it makes much sense.
It should be `f : ‚àÄ a, Œ≥ a ‚Üí Œ¥ a`, I think?

`List.map` takes in a non-dependent `Œ± ‚Üí Œ≤` argument, so I don't think that works.

Unfortunately I don't have any actual use case for this second lemma to test against. I'm just adding it for symmetry with the first one.
It works just fine, see the commit I just pushed. While `f` is dependent, the function passed to `List.map` is not.
